[DQC.US.0178.10137] The filing includes a value for dividends using the concept us-gaap:StockIssuedDuringPeriodValueStockDividend with a value of 158,333. This value represents a dividend paid in stock, but no impact has been reported on the value of APIC. If this is an actual dividend paid in stock it should include the retained earnings member and not have a value in the default. If it is a dividend paid fully in cash then the element DividendsCommonStockCash should be used. If it is partial stock and cash then the element DividendsCommonStock should be used.
